# Support for {{ repoName }}

> {{ shortdesc }}

Thank you for using {{ repoName }}! This document explains how to get help and
report problems.

---

## Asking Questions

For general usage questions, ideas, or discussion, please open a
**[GitHub Discussion]({{ homepage | default(value="https://github.com/" ~ repoName) }}/discussions)**
so the community can benefit from the answer.

## Reporting Bugs

Before filing a new bug, search the existing issues to avoid duplicates.

**Issue tracker:** {% if bugTracker %}{{ bugTracker }}{% else %}{{ homepage | default(value="https://github.com/" ~ repoName) }}/issues{% endif %}

When reporting a bug please include:

- A clear, concise description of the problem
- Steps to reproduce the behaviour
- Expected vs actual output
- Version information (`{{ repoName }} --version` / `cargo --version`)
- Operating system and architecture

## Security Vulnerabilities

Please do **not** open a public issue for security vulnerabilities.

Contact the maintainer directly{% if authorEmail %} at **{{ authorEmail }}**{% endif %}
or follow the project's `SECURITY.md` if present.

## Feature Requests

Feature requests are welcome. Open an issue in the tracker above and use the
**enhancement** label. Describe the use-case you are trying to solve rather
than just the solution you have in mind.

## Commercial Support

{{ repoName }} is an open-source project maintained on a best-effort basis.
{% if authorName %}If you need priority support or a commercial arrangement, reach out to
**{{ authorName }}**{% if authorEmail %} ({{ authorEmail }}){% endif %}.{% else %}No
commercial support is currently available.{% endif %}

